      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BLESSED RAIN (4) has an excellent record here having never missed the placings in 10 starts, including nine wins. Recorded a 4 length win (21.73) in a Free For All last time at Shepparton. Makes strong appeal on best. BALLISTIC BLAZE (2) jumped from a low draw and boxed on well to finish second last time, beaten 0.8 lengths (22.83) behind Why Not Iris at this track. The form out of last race has been strong. Expected to feature. BULL DURHAM (8) has a fair record and proved too classy last time to win by 3.5 lengths at this track in a handy 22.82 beating Kenzie Kid. Goes well out of this box with a win and four minor placings. Leading chance again. DR. WILL (1) racing over this distance brings the best out in him.",
